$SPY $QQQ $AAPL $TVIX $WMT Most powerful tool FOMC has is the bully pulpit! While the swap lines in place can increase funding, money velocity is an entirely different beast, demands confidence. While M2 supply has increased on books, M2 velocity has yet to follow. Not exactly printing press. Remember: QE is the swap of one USD asset (Treasuries) for a shorter one (Bank Reserves). It doesn’t add dollars to the "system". Additionally dollar swap lines don’t add USD to the system either. They simply add USD funding to the system. Those two are very different outcomes. Just because USD funding rises, doesn&39;t mean money velocity rises. For that, it takes funding confidence. Much of what floats around  financial and social media are false narratives. Get your facts!

Since then, the stock is up 43%. Yet, he didn’t entirely miss out on the rally. Meeks still owns shares in his clients’ portfolios as an underweight because he knows he’s being judged versus the tech benchmarks. Plus, he still views Apple as an “iconic” company.  But he has no plans to buy more Apple shares unless they fall at least 40% from current levels.
